lass=\"layoutArea\">\r\n<div class=\"column\">\r\n\r\nThis 3 cube unit on 2 levels was stripped down to the concrete and totally renovated into a fabulous State-of-the-art space that is in keeping with some details of the building\'s heritage as design features.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nThis property has been featured in several Montreal design magazines showcasing the beautiful aesthetics of this bright, airy space...from room to room the superb views are a show stopper!\r\n\r\nThe monthly fees include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Municipal and school taxes.</li>\r\n 	<li>Heating</li>\r\n 	<li>Air conditioning</li>\r\n 	<li>Electricity</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintenance</li>\r\n 	<li>Repair</li>\r\n 	<li>Building insurance</li>\r\n 	<li>Shuttle bus downtown 6 days/week</li>\r\n 	<li>24 hour security</li>\r\n 	<li>Depanneur in the complex open 7 days/week</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nList of improvements include:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>New windows</li>\r\n 	<li>New heating, a/c system</li>\r\n 	<li>New plumbing</li>\r\n 	<li>New electrical</li>\r\n 	<li>New Bamboo floors (heated floors in all bathrooms) -New insulation</li>\r\n 	<li>All beautifully customized (millwork) wood built-ins.</li>\r\n 	<li>Habitat 67 Tennis Club in clay courts with instructor.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHabitat\'67 is a Limited Partnership and the General Partner will look after the transfer of title with a cost of 1 % of the sale price, payable by the Buyer to the Partnership. However, there is no welcome tax. Also, there are no notary costs pertaining to the transfer of title, except in the event of financing.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nHabitat\'67 was cited as a heritage building by the city of Montreal in September 2007, and declared a heritage building by the Government of Quebec in February 2009 in relation to the outside of the Complex as well as to the inside of the 4 cubes that belong to the architect, renowned internationally, Mr. Moshe Safdie.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 2\">\r\n<div class=\"section\">\r\n<div cla